    {
      "id": "56ef3b60e393a6897a5b8644848a39172730e230",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-10-05 03:01:53.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\n> Andriy - I agree that recovery-small test 101 needs to restore this\n > parameter, but I'd rather the test itself clean up after itself on\n > error. One way to do this would be to set a trap that restores the\n > parameter on error.\n\nUsing stack_trap() is the best way to handle conditions like this.  We don't want a remote shell command at the end of every test to fix up a parameter that is only changed by one or a few tests.  That would quickly lead to a lot of needless complexity and slowdown in the cleanup, if it were done this way for every test.\n\nIn any case, it looks like the stack_trap was added as part of patch https://review.whamcloud.com/33557 \"LU-11601 ptlrpc: IR doesn't reconnect after EAGAIN\", so this patch is no longer needed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    }
